{"id": 1694, "title": "Ticket #1694: BaseResource batch status timer not canceled in destructor", "description": "<blockquote>\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=939\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('939'); return false;\" title=\"Issue single status command for all cream jobs\">#939</a></span> added support in the gridmanager's <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=BaseResource\" title=\"Base Resource\">BaseResource</a></span> object to do a status query for all the jobs of a given resource. This involves registering a daemoncore timer. That timer isn't canceled when the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=BaseResource\" title=\"Base Resource\">BaseResource</a></span> is deleted. This can lead to a crash of the gridmanager when daemoncore calls the timer on a deleted object.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2010-Oct-06 12:29:37 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\nPushed a commit to V7_5_4-branch for 7.5.4. The timer is now canceled appropriately.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Oct-06 13:45</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d0c93e5806344b055fdf19b300d09d7116751676\">[19125]</a></span>: Cancel batch status timer in <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=BaseResource\" title=\"Base Resource\">BaseResource</a></span> destructor, part 2. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=1694\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1694'); return false;\" title=\"BaseResource batch status timer not canceled in destructor\">#1694</a></span> Missed a spot in previous c